<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04928</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING UNION ORGANIZATION AND DISALLOWING CANCELLATION OF UNION REGISTRATION, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, AS AMENDED, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : " Union Formation Act "</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides that independent union or a local/chapter has only to give notice of its creation to the DOLE to acquire legal personality; Removes the twenty percent minimum membership requirement for creation of independent union and lowers to two, the ten unions or locals for federation or national unions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>MENDOZA, RAYMUND DEMOCRITO C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-02-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2018-03-22)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB08186</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2017-02-08</td></tr></table>